-- Almarai Co., Al-Khodari Sons, Saudi Dairy: Saudi Equity Preview
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-03-31T08:13:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-31/almarai-co-al-khodari-sons-saudi-dairy-saudi-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Saudi Arabia’s market. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  The  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  gained 0.2% to 7,782.84 on
March 28.  Almarai Co. (ALMARAI)  : Saudi Arabia’s largest food
producer by market value raised its stake in a joint venture
with PepsiCo Inc. to 52 percent from 48 percent. The shares
advanced 2.2 percent to 114 riyals, the highest since January
2011.  Abdullah A.M. Al-Khodari Sons Co. (ALKHODAR)  : The
contactor won a contract valued at 26.8 million riyals ($7.1
million) from the Ministry of Higher Education to build a
college. The shares declined 0.5 percent to 54.5 riyals.  Saudi Dairy & Foodstuff Co. (SADAFCO)  : The company
received 4.1 million riyals from its 2.75 percent return on a
150 million-riyal Islamic deposit with United Gulf Bank. The
shares fell 0.4 percent to 57 riyals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
